        <section class="content-intro">

            <div class="infobox_d">
                <p>Steel is one of the most important building materials of our
                    time.
                    Steel buildings are resistant to natural and artificial
                    wear
                    and
                    which has made this material ubiquitous throughout the
                    world.
                    To improve the efficiency of steel production, this program
                    will
                    help to
                    identify defects.</p>
                <p>In this program was used an algorithm by
                    <strong><em>localizing</em></strong>
                    and <strong><em>classifying</em></strong> surface defects
                    on a
                    steel
                    plate.</p>
                <details open>
                    <summary>Dataset Description:</summary>
                    <ul>
                        <li id="index1">Defects must be segmented and
                            classified
                            in the
                            test
                            set.
                        </li>
                        <li>Each image may have no defects, a defect of a
                            single
                            class,
                            or
                            defects of multiple classes.
                        </li>
                        <li>For each image must be segment defects of each
                            class
                            (ClassId =
                            [1, 2, 3, 4]).
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </details>
                <p>You can find more details <a
                        href="https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/severstal-steel-defect-detection/overview"
                        target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">here</a></p>
            </div>
        </section>
